President Biden addressed a crowd in Cleveland, Ohio, thanking them for their support and discussing the importance of unions and retirement security. He highlighted the passage of the Butch Lewis Act, which protects pensions for millions of workers and retirees, and criticized Republicans for their opposition to the legislation. Biden also criticized Republican plans to privatize Social Security and cut healthcare benefits. He emphasized his commitment to the middle class and promised to be a pro-labor and pro-union President.